# Messy Virgo Website Workflow

Public static Eleventy + Tailwind site. Always follow these boundaries and steps.

## Source Boundaries
- Edit **only** source files: `*.html`, `about/**/*.html`, `legal/**/*.html`, `dapps/**/*.html`, `blog/**/*.njk`, `_blog/_posts/**/*.md`, `_includes/**/*.njk`, `css/**/*.css`, `js/**/*.js`, config/docs.
- Never hand-edit `_site/` (generated, gitignored) or `css/tailwind.css` (generated; always rebuild).
- Do not add dependencies unless explicitly requested and truly required.

## Commands
- `npm ci` – install
- `npm run build:css` – Tailwind only
- `npm run build` – full site (CSS + Eleventy)
- Preview: `npm run dev` (Tailwind watch + Eleventy), or `npm run watch:css` + `npm run serve` in separate terminals.

## Required Verification (non-negotiable)
- Any change to Tailwind classes (HTML/Nunjucks/MD/JS), `css/**/*.css`, or `tailwind.config.js` → run `npm run build:css`.
- Before finishing any source change → run `npm run build`.
- Visual changes → preview the public URL at both mobile and desktop widths.

## Typography (www)

- **Inter** for body and all default headings (`css/base.css`).
- **Gradient titles:** `font-bold font-sans tracking-tight` + `text-gradient` in templates; blog TOC injection matches this (`_includes/post.njk`).
- **`.font-serif` (Playfair):** optional only; do not use for routine section titles.

## Specialized Skills
- Blog posts → `publish-blog-post`
- Weekly build logs → `messyvirgo-weekly-buildlog`
- General page edits → `messyvirgo-edit-webpage`
